ON Friday Tholinhlanhla Primary School held a memorial service for Winnie Madikizela-Mandela. Teachers and pupils gathered for a prayer and pupils delivered speeches about mama Winnie Madikizela-Mandela, who was bold and beautiful. Invited guests mama Girly Ngcobo who opened with a prayer and Mamsie Mkhize talked about the South African flag which was flying half-mast in honour of mama Winnie and the importance of a social worker in the community. Female teachers and pupils wore “doeks” to show respect just as mama Winnie did. — Supplied: Media Committee 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  